00:12:05.110 --> 00:12:07.610
&gt;&gt; W. Douglas Fisher:
Thank you for coming.

00:12:07.610 --> 00:12:11.360
Now prior to World War I
the U.S. Army was tiny.

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:15.920 position:56%
I mean, 200,000 people spread around
the world and around this country.

00:12:15.920 --> 00:12:18.400
And it was totally segregated.

00:12:18.400 --> 00:12:21.830
Black officers were
virtually non-existent.

00:12:21.830 --> 00:12:29.570 position:56%
Nevertheless, between 1917 and 1919,
400,000 African American men served.

00:12:29.570 --> 00:12:32.720
Most of them were in
labor and support units.

00:12:32.720 --> 00:12:35.980
But 10 thous-- , 10 percent, or
40,000 of these troops served

00:12:35.980 --> 00:12:38.940
in the combat units that
we've talked about, the 92nd

00:12:38.940 --> 00:12:42.540
and the 93rd divisions in France.

00:12:42.540 --> 00:12:46.160
The black officers were
trained at Fort Des Moines Iowa,

00:12:46.160 --> 00:12:50.740
with 639 line officers completing
a special officers' training camp,

00:12:50.740 --> 00:12:52.400
only done once.

00:12:52.400 --> 00:12:55.000
And 104 doctors, who
we're writing about,

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:58.620
completed the medical officers'
training camp that was there.

00:12:58.620 --> 00:13:00.820
Things had been written about
the officers' training camp,

00:13:00.820 --> 00:13:04.270
but not the medical officers,
and we uncovered that.

00:13:04.270 --> 00:13:07.490
Training for the doctors was
rigorous, with a 10-mile march

00:13:07.490 --> 00:13:10.630
and a three-day outdoor encampment.

00:13:10.630 --> 00:13:13.840
In this picture that you can see
here, this is a picture of the guys

00:13:13.840 --> 00:13:17.380
out in their tents at the
encampment on the state fairgrounds

00:13:17.380 --> 00:13:20.260
and you can see the
rollercoaster in the background.

00:13:20.260 --> 00:13:24.270
I don't think they were
having a lot of fun, though.

00:13:24.270 --> 00:13:28.100
These doctors were also given
command of the medical detachments

00:13:28.100 --> 00:13:33.640 position:56%
with 10 enlisted men in each of the
detachments, saving some leadership.

00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:37.300
After the MOTC training, the
doctors were assigned to the 92nd

00:13:37.300 --> 00:13:39.990
or 93rd Divisions and spread

00:13:39.990 --> 00:13:45.070
across eight different U.S.
encampments across the country.

00:13:46.310 --> 00:13:50.950
Then in 1918, the combat
units were sent to France.

00:13:50.950 --> 00:13:55.410
The 93rd Division, which
consisted of 12,000 soldiers

00:13:55.410 --> 00:14:00.290
and four national guard
regiments arrived overseas first.

00:14:00.290 --> 00:14:04.670
The French wanted American troops
to fill its decimated ranks.

00:14:04.670 --> 00:14:08.890
So General Pershing gave him the
93rd Division, the four regiments

00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:12.080
of that, and the French loved it.

00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:14.010
They were terrific.

00:14:14.010 --> 00:14:17.490
They fought more time, one of
the units there fought longer

00:14:17.490 --> 00:14:21.230
than any other American
unit in combat.

00:14:21.230 --> 00:14:25.330
The 92nd Buffalo Division,
consisting of 27,000 men,

00:14:25.330 --> 00:14:30.730
arrived in mid-1918 and fought with
the American 1st and 2nd armies.

00:14:30.730 --> 00:14:32.900
That's the unit that my
grandfather served in.

00:14:32.900 --> 00:14:38.790
The 104 doctors were assigned to
frontline medical detachments,

00:14:38.790 --> 00:14:44.630
ambulance companies, and field
hospitals, right up front.

00:14:44.630 --> 00:14:49.640
They endured combat and suffered
aerial and artillery attacks.

00:14:49.640 --> 00:14:52.940
Many were wounded from the
effects of exploding gas shells.

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:56.010
Gas was a terrible
problem in World War I.

00:14:56.010 --> 00:14:58.080
One doctor was killed in field.

00:14:58.080 --> 00:15:00.680
His grandsons are with
us here today.

00:15:02.680 --> 00:15:07.620 position:56%
Interesting, almost as many American
soldiers died of disease as died

00:15:07.620 --> 00:15:10.920
in combat in World War I.

00:15:10.920 --> 00:15:14.000
Army doctors such as
ours faced both the enemy

00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:18.150
and killer diseases including the
horrendous Spanish flu epidemic

00:15:18.150 --> 00:15:22.920
of 1918 that killed tens of
millions of people worldwide.

